This list contains Germanic elements of the English language which have a close
corresponding Latinate form.  The correspondence is
semanticâin most cases these words are not cognates, but in some cases they are
doublets, i.e., ultimately derived from the same root, generally Proto-Indo-
European, as in cow and beef, both ultimately from PIE *gÊ·Åus.

The meanings of these words do not always correspond to Germanic cognates, and
occasionally the specific meaning in the list is unique to English.
